//]]&gt;
</script>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p>Buzzfeed recently teamed up with HBO on the &quot;How would you die in Game of Thrones Quiz&quot; it got over a million hits. It’s a very effective ad for Game of Thrones and, as it turns out, a very effective data mining tool.</p>"},{"content":"<p>&quot;It’s a tool for advertisers to understand us better masquerading as a tool for us to understand ourselves better,&quot; says Aram Sinnreich, a media professor at Rutgers University and author of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/1625340524" target="_blank">The Piracy Crusade: How the Music Industry&apos;s War on Sharing Destroys Markets and Erodes Civil Liberties</a>.</p>","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<p>As Sinnreich explains, not only does HBO now know I watch Game of Thrones, in taking the quiz, I gave them a lot of information. My preferred alcohol: <a href="http://giphy.com/gifs/sPZdjmGJxJWaA" target="_blank">white wine</a>. My last meal: <a href="http://giphy.com/gifs/CwL2BOuRlVSnK" target="_blank">a steak</a>. My biggest fear: <a href="http://giphy.com/gifs/jBvPmuBuzmjzW" target="_blank">failure</a>. My idea of heaven: <a href="http://giphy.com/gifs/ys25zLolNge9G" target="_blank">A tropical beach</a>.</p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p>That is hugely valuable information.</p>"},{"content":"<p>&quot;That’s the brilliance of this plan,&quot; says Sinnreich. &quot;Instead of us reluctantly agreeing to give marketers information about ourselves, we are emphatically proclaiming to marketers who we are and then demanding that our friends do the same.&quot;</p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p>Sinnreich says the quiz fad will probably fade, but the economic need for marketers to get more information on us will not. He expects we’ll see more tools that will make handing over information about ourselves into <a href="http://giphy.com/gifs/uHccXYrGRIFNe" target="_blank">a game</a>.</p>"}]
